{
  "text": "and a appropriate solution is The others are negative or not real. g m is a critical value, that is to say, when g > g m , there is just a black hole without the second-order phase transition. Phase transition will be turned on while g ≤ g m . As we know, parameter g is the monopole charge of a self-gravitating magnetic field described by a nonlinear electrodynamics [CITATION_1] .",
